* Iron lifted a brow and smiled.  < That's COMMANDER.>
But then she turned her eyes towards Nightstrike, her eyes turning with a 
sly glint, making her smile seem evil.
< But bring him down to me, Prowl. Down were I can get him.>
Her inner thoughts reflected carnage, mech-fluid and gears. And the 
screaming of enemy bots.  A side which she always kept hidden, and this 
would be the firxt time that Prowl would see into her bloot thirsty nature.
It was almost as if the thoughts fueled her, the image of her stripping the 
cybertronic flesh off of enemy transformers super structures flashing in her 
mine in one instant. Every single enemy, screaming.  And a feeling of 
excitement flowed along those images, of eagerness.*
